    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 13329/1–3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Root instructs Mr. O’Brien to convey appropriate expressions of the
                    President’s and Government’s sympathy with the Japanese Government in the
                    terrible disaster resulting from the explosion on the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Matsushima.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
